casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellant, v. Caulley, Appellee.

[Cite as State v. Caulley, 136 Ohio St.3d 325, 2013-Ohio-3673.]

(No. 2012-1974 — Submitted August 21, 2013 — Decided September 5, 2013.)

{¶ 1} The judgment of the court of appeals is affirmed on the authority of State v. Forrest, 136 Ohio St.3d 134, 2013-Ohio-2409, 991 N.E.2d 1124.

O’Connor, C.J., and Pfeifer, Lanzinger, French, and O’Neill, JJ., concur. O’Donnell and Kennedy, JJ., dissent. *326Ron O’Brien, Franklin County Prosecuting Attorney, and Seth L. Gilbert, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellant. Timothy Young, Ohio Public Defender, and Kimberly S. Rigby, Assistant Public Defender, for appellee.
